title: Ask HN: How do you set up a system to track customer's usage in AWS?
text:
Hello,

I have created a tool on top of AWS Textract(a OCR tool). I am trying to add a paid tier account but I am not sure how to set up tracking of usage or what the term for this is called to begin to google resources for it. Googling tracking usage in aws only brings up personal tracking of cloud costs.

Thank you!

title: Remember Monochrome Screens?
text: What happened to them? I remember how much I loved the old screens on the iPod before they went color only, it was washed out and very ugly. The iPod I had would appear crisp and readable in the daytime, has a nice backlight and the battery was good if it didn’t have an HDD. I saw the remarkable topic and just thought about the old ebook readers with monochrome screens. I’d prefer one to eink: fast refresh, visible in the daytime and non distracting.

Ask HN: What can I do to start reading again?
text:
I have tried reading things I like (science fiction) and technical books, but for some reason I cannot seem to focus and complete them. It is very difficult for me to read more than 15-20 pages after I sit down to read.

I believe reading is a skill and a habit, and that building the habit matters more than trying to seem smart reading a technical book like I should.

TLDR: would reading Animorphs series or something stupid help me more than reading a technical book? Should I try to isolate and read quietly, or train myself to read with the TV on to a game or something to practice focusing? Does anyone have anecdotal evidence going from a non-reader to being a reader?

How do you go from here (illiterate) to there (reading books 24/7)?

Viewpoint on Patents
text:
I'm a former USPTO primary patent examiner in computer related areas (don't hate me, I personally thought the system was broken more so than anyone else). However, I'm out now and I view patents as just part of the game; and as long as these are the rules, patents should be taken into account.

I want to start some sort of scalable project around helping startups at YC level type stage at least become educated on getting basic IP started and/or just start getting some easily. Maybe automate as much of the system as I can. I remember a YC company called Clerky, maybe something similar to that. Would you use such a thing? What kind of price/business model would you engage with?

Show HN: AnySelfie – AI Art Seflies for the Masses
text:
Howdy HN! I had a lot of fun putting myself into different universes (Apollo 11, Hulk, Wild West, Dr Strange) using Dreambooth and Stable Diffusion. I'm curious to see if there is an appetite for this type of entertainment app.

My vision is pre-configured prompts and pre-generating images, so people can explore it like a selfieverse feed. For technical users, I would offer them to download the 2GB model so that can own it and run their own prompts. Long term, maybe open up the prompt UI for technical users.

Another goal was to re-learn Rust. This UI is built in Yew (Rust, CSS, and HTML only) and the backend is in Actix. It has been a great practical project for getting practice with the language.

Thank you for the feedback!
